obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46458)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The word "Indian" omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46458&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the ^1*** Divorce Act, and shall`
  line `come into operation on the first day of April, 1869.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46377)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Extent of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46377&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[This Act extends to ^2[the whole of India ^3[except the state of Jammu and`
  line Kashmir^*]].]
  line
  line `Extent of power to grant relief generally.-- ^4[Nothing hereinafter contained shall`
  line `authorise any Court to grant any relief under this Act except where the petitioner ^5[or`
  line `respondent professes the Christian religion],`
  line
  line `and to make decrees of dissolution.--or to make decrees of dissolution of marriage except where`
  line `the parties to the marriage are domiciled in India at the time when the petition is presented,`
  line
  line `or of nullity--.or to make decrees of nullity of marriage except where the marriage has`
  line `been solemnized in India and the petitioner is resident in India at the time of presenting the`
  line petition,
  line
  line `or to grant any relief under this Act, other than a decree of dissolution of marriage or of`
  line `nullity of marriage, except where the petitioner resides in India at the time of presenting the`
  line petition].
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. 1948, for first paragraph`
  line
  line `2. Subs by A.O. 1950, for certain words.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for except Part B States.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 1926, s. 2, for paras. 2, 3 and 4.`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 30 of 1927, s. 2.`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46378)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46378&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there be something repugnant in the subject or`
  line `context, --`
  line
  line `^1[(1) "High Court".-- "High Court" means with reference to any area:--`
  line
  line `(a) in a State, the High Court for that State;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) in Delhi, the High Court of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(bb) in Himachal Pradesh, the High Court of Punjab and Haryana up to and inclusive of the`
  line `30th April, 1967 and the High Court of Delhi thereafter];`
  line
  line `(c) in Manipur and Tripura, the High Court of Assam;`
  line
  line `(d) in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands, the High Court at Calcutta;`
  line
  line `(e) in ^3[Lakshadweep], the High Court of Kerala;`
  line
  line `^4[(ee) in Chandigarh, the High Court of Punjab and Haryana];`
  line
  line `and in the case of any petition under this Act, "High Court" means the High Court for the area where`
  line `the husband and wife reside or last resided together;`
  line
  line `^5[(2) "District Judge" means a Judge of a principal civil court of original jurisdiction however`
  line `designated]:`
  line
  line `(3) "District Court" means, in the case of any petition under this Act, the court of the District`
  line `Judge within the local limits of whose ordinary jurisdiction, ^6[or of whose jurisdiction under this Act`
  line `the marriage was solemnized or] the husband and wife reside or last resided together;`
  line
  line `(4) "Court" means the High Court or the District Court, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(5) "minor children" means, in the case of sons of Native fathers, boy, who have not completed`
  line `the age of sixteen years, and, in the case of daughters of Native fathers, girls who have not completed`
  line `the age of thirteen years; In other cases it means unmarried children who have not completed the age`
  line `of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `^7**** *`
  line
  line `^8* * * **`
  line
  line `(8) "marriage with another woman" means marriage of any person, being married, to any other`
  line `person, during the life of the former wife, whether the second marriage shall have taken place`
  line `within ^9[India] or elsewhere;`
  line
  line `(9) "desertion", implies an abandonment against the wish of the person charging it; and`
  line
  line `(10) "property" includes in the case of a wife, any property to which she is entitled for an estate in`
  line `remainder or reversion or as a trustee, executrix or administratrix; and the date of the death of the`
  line `testator or intestate shall be deemed to be the time at which any such wife becomes entitled as`
  line `executrix or administratrix.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Adaption of Laws (No. 2) 1956, for clause (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Himachal Pradesh (Adaptation of Laws on State and Concurrent Subjects) Order, 1968, for sub-clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-11-`
  line `1966).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands (Alteration of Name) Adaptation of Laws Order, 1974, for "the Laccadive,`
  line `Minicoy and Amindivi Islands" (w.e.f. 1-11-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by the Punjab Reorganisation (Chandigarh) (Adaptation of Laws on State and Concurrent Subjects) Order, 1968 (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for clause (2).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 3, for "or of whose jurisdiction under this Act" (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line
  line `7. Clause (6) omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line
  line `8. Clause (7) omitted by s. 3, ibid, (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the dominions of Her Majesty".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46379)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Matrimonial jurisdiction of High Courts to be exercised subject to Act. Exception.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46379&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line The
  line `jurisdiction now exercised by the High Courts in respect of divorce a mensa et toro, and in all other`
  line `causes, suits and matters matrimonial, shall be exercised by such courts and by the District Courts`
  line `subject to the provisions in this Act contained, and not otherwise; except so far as relates to the`
  line `granting of marriage-licenses, which may be granted as if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46380)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Enforcement of decrees or orders made heretofore by Supreme or High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46380&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any decree or order of the late Supreme Court of Judicature at Calcutta, Madras or Bombay sitting on`
  line `the ecclesiastical side, or of any of the said High Courts sitting in the exercise of their matrimonial`
  line `jurisdiction, respectively, in any cause or matter matrimonial, may be enforced and dealt with by the`
  line `said High Courts, respectively, as hereinafter mentioned, in like manner as if such decree or order had`
  line `been originally made under this Act by the Court so enforcing or dealing with the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46381)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Pending suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46381&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `All suits and proceedings in causes and matters matrimonial, which when this`
  line `Act comes into operation are pending in any High Court, shall be dealt with and decided by such`
  line `court, so far as may be, as if they had been originally instituted therein under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46382)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46382&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `[Court to act on principles of English Divorce Court.]––Omitted by the Indian Divorce`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2001 (51 of 2001), s. 4 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46383)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Extraordinary jurisdiction of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46383&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, whenever it thinks fit,`
  line `remove and try and determine as a Court of original jurisdiction any suit or proceeding instituted`
  line `under this Act in the Court of any District Judge within the limits of its jurisdiction under this Act.`
  line
  line `Power to transfer suits.The High Court may also withdraw any such suit or proceeding, and transfer it for trial or disposal to the Court of any other such District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46384)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Reference to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46384&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `When any question of law or usage having the force of law arises`
  line `at any point in the proceedings previous to the hearing of any suit under this Act by a District Court or`
  line `at any subsequent stage of such suit, or in the execution of the decree therein or order thereon,`
  line
  line `the Court may, either of its own motion or on the application of any of the parties, draw up a`
  line `statement of the case and refer it, with the Courts own opinion thereon, to the decision of the High`
  line Court.
  line
  line `If the question has arisen previous to or in the hearing, the District Court may either stay such`
  line `proceedings, or proceed in the case pending such reference, and pass a decree contingent upon the`
  line `opinion of the High Court upon it.`
  line
  line `If a decree or order has been made, its execution shall be stayed until the receipt of the order of the`
  line `High Court upon such reference.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46466)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Grounds for dissolution of marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46466&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Grounds for dissolution of marriage.--(1) Any marriage solemnized, whether before or`
  line `after the commencement of the Indian Divorce (Amendment) Act, 2001 (51 of 2001), may, on a`
  line `petition presented to the District Court either by the husband or the wife, be dissolved on the ground`
  line `that since the solemnization of the marriage, the respondent---`
  line
  line `(i) has committed adultery; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has ceased to be Christian by conversion to another religion; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has been incurably of unsound mind for a continuous period of not less than two years`
  line `immediately preceding the presentation of the petition; or`
  line
  line ^2******
  line
  line `(v) has, for a period of not less than two years immediately preceding the presentation of the`
  line `petition, been suffering from venereal disease in a communicable form; or`
  line
  line `(vi) has not been heard of as being alive for a period of seven years or more by those persons`
  line `who would naturally have heard of the respondent if the respondent had been alive; or`
  line
  line `(vii) has wilfully refused to consummate the marriage and the marriage has not therefore been`
  line `consummated; or`
  line
  line `(viii) has failed to comply with a decree for restitution of conjugal rights for a period of two`
  line `years or upwards after the passing of the decree against the respondent; or`
  line
  line `(ix) has deserted the petitioner for at least two years immediately preceding the presentation of`
  line `the petition; or`
  line
  line `(x) has treated the petitioner with such cruelty as to cause a reasonable apprehension in the`
  line `mind of the petitioner that it would be harmful or injurious for the petitioner to live with the`
  line respondent.
  line
  line `(2) A wife may also present a petition for the dissolution of her marriage on the ground that the`
  line `husband has, since the solemnization of the marriage, been guilty of rape, sodomy or bestiality.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 5, for section 10 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (iv) omitted by Act 6 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (46906)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Dissolution of marriage by mutual consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 6. (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46906&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act`
  line `and the rules made thereunder, a petition for dissolution of marriage may be presented to the District`
  line `Court by both the parties to a marriage together, whether such marriage was solemnized before or`
  line `after the commencement of the Indian Divorce (Amendment) Act, 2001 (51 of 2001), on the ground`
  line `that they have been living separately for a period of two years or more, that they have not been able to`
  line `live together and they have mutually agreed that the marriage should be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) On the motion of both the parties made not earlier than six months after the date of presentation`
  line `of the petition referred to in sub-section (1) and not later than eighteen months after the said date, if`
  line `the petition is not withdrawn by both the parties in the mean time, the Court shall, on being satisfied,`
  line `after hearing the parties and making such inquiry, as it thinks fit, that a marriage has been solemnized`
  line `and that the averments in the petition are true, pass a decree declaring the marriage to be dissolved`
  line `with effect from the date of decree.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46386)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Adulterer to be co-respondent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for section 11 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46386&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Adulterer or adulteress to be co-respondent---On a petition for dissolution of marriage`
  line `presented by a husband or wife on the ground of adultery, the petitioner shall make the alleged`
  line `adulterer or adulteress a co-respondent, unless the petitioner is excused by the Court from so doing on`
  line `any of the following grounds, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) that the wife, being the respondent is leading the life of a prostitute or the husband, being`
  line `respondent is leading an immoral life and that the petitioner knows of no person with whom the`
  line `adultery has been committed;`
  line
  line `(b) that the name of the alleged adulterer or adulteress is unknown to the petitioner although`
  line `the petitioner has made due efforts to discover it;`
  line
  line `(c) that the alleged adulterer or adulteress is dead].`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46387)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Court to be satisfied of absence of collusion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46387&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Upon any such petition for the dissolution of`
  line `a marriage, the Court shall satisfy itself, so far as it reasonably can, not only as to the facts alleged,`
  line `but also whether or not the petitioner has been in any manner accessory to, or conniving at, the going`
  line `through of the said form of marriage, or the adultery, or has condoned the same, and shall also enquire`
  line `into any countercharge which may be made against the petitioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46388)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Dismissal of petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Last paragraph of section 13 omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46388&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `In case the Court, on the evidence in relation to any such petition, is`
  line `satisfied that the petitioner's case has not been proved, or is not satisfied that the alleged adultery has`
  line `been committed,`
  line
  line `or finds that the petitioner has, during the marriage, been accessory to, or conniving at, the going`
  line `through of the said form of marriage, or the adultery of the other party to the marriage, or has`
  line `condoned the adultery complained of,`
  line
  line `or that the petition is presented or prosecuted in collusion with either of the respondents,`
  line
  line `then and in any of the said cases the Court shall dismiss the petition.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46389)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to Court to pronounce decree for dissolving marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46389&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `In case the Court is`
  line `satisfied on the evidence that the case of the petitioner has been proved,`
  line
  line `and does not find that the petitioner has been in any manner accessory to, or conniving at, the`
  line `going through of the said form of marriage, or the adultery of the other party to the marriage, or has`
  line `condoned the adultery complained of,`
  line
  line `or that the petition is presented or prosecuted in collusion with either of the respondents,`
  line
  line `the Court shall pronounce a decree declaring such marriage to be dissolved ^1***:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court shall not be bound to pronounce such decree if it finds that the petitioner`
  line `has, during the marriage, been guilty of adultery,`
  line
  line `or if the petitioner has, in the opinion of the Court, been guilty of unreasonable delay in presenting`
  line `or prosecuting such petition,`
  line
  line `or of cruelty towards the other party to the marriage,`
  line
  line `or of having deserted or wilfully separated himself or herself from the other party before the`
  line `adultery complained of, and without reasonable excuse,`
  line
  line `or of such wilful neglect or misconduct of or towards the other party as has conduced to the`
  line adultery.
  line
  line `Condonation. No adultery shall be deemed to have been condoned within the meaning of this Act`
  line `unless where conjugal cohabitation has been resumed or continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "in the manner and subject to all the provisions and limitation in section 16 and 17 made declared" in`
  line `paragraph 4 of section 14 omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 9 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46390)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Relief in case of opposition on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46390&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `In any suit instituted for dissolution of`
  line `marriage, if the respondent opposes the relief sought on the ground, in case of such a suit instituted by`
  line `a husband, of his adultery, cruelty, or desertion ^1`
  line `*** or, in case of such a suit instituted by a wife, on`
  line `the ground of ^2[her adultery or cruelty or desertion], the Court may in such suit give to the respondent,`
  line `on his or her application, the same relief to which he or she would have been entitled in case he or she`
  line `had presented a petition seeking such relief, and the respondent shall be competent to give evidence of`
  line `or relating to ^3[such adultery, cruelty] or desertion.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "without reasonable excuse," omitted by s. 10, ibid., (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "her adultery and cruelty" (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "such cruelty" (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46391)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Decrees for dissolution to be nisi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. The words "not being a confirmation of a decree of a District Court" omitted by s. 11, ibid., (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46391&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Every decree for dissolution of marriage made by a`
  line `High Court ^1*** shall in the first instance, be a decree nisi, not to be made absolute till after the`
  line `expiration of such time, not less than six months from the pronouncing thereof, as the High Court, by`
  line `general or special order from time to time, directs.`
  line
  line `Collusion. During that period any person shall be at liberty, in such manner as the High Court by`
  line `general or special order from time to time directs, to show cause why the said decree should not be`
  line `made absolute by reason of the same having been obtained by collusion or by reason of material facts`
  line `not being brought before the Court.`
  line
  line `On cause being so shown, the Court shall deal with the case by making the decree absolute, or by`
  line `reversing the decree nisi, or by requiring further inquiry, or otherwise as justice may demand.`
  line
  line `The High Court may order the cost of Counsel and witnesses and otherwise arising from such`
  line `cause being shown, to be paid by the parties or such one or more of them as it thinks fit, including a`
  line `wife if she have separate property.`
  line
  line `Whenever a decree nisi has been made, and the petitioner fails, within a reasonable time, to move`
  line `to have such decree made absolute, the High Court may dismiss the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46392)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of High Court to remove certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 17 (w.e.f 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46392&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Power of High Court to remove certain suits.—During the progress of the suit in the`
  line `Court of the District Judge, any person suspecting that any parties to the suit are or have been acting`
  line `in collusion for the purpose of obtaining a divorce, shall be at liberty, in such manner as the High`
  line `Court by general or special order from time to time directs, to apply to the High Court to remove the`
  line `suit under section 8, and the Court shall thereupon, if it thinks fit, remove such suit and try and`
  line `determine the same as a Court of original jurisdiction, and the provisions contained in section 16 shall`
  line `apply to every suit so removed; or it may direct the District Judge to take such steps in respect of the`
  line `alleged collusion as may be necessary, to enable him to make a decree in accordance with the justice`
  line `of the case].`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (46393)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 19
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46393&sectionno=17A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `[Appointment of officer to exercise duties of King's Proctor.]Omitted by the Indian`
  line `Divorce (Amendment) Act, 2001 (51 of 2001), s. 13 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46465)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Petition for decree of nullity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or to the High Court" omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 14 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46465&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Any husband or wife may present a petition to the District`
  line `Court ^1`
  line `***, praying that his or her marriage may be declared null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (46395)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Grounds of decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "jurisdiction of the High Court" (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46395&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Such decree may be made on any of the following grounds:---`
  line
  line `(1) that the respondent was impotent at the time of the marriage and at the time of the`
  line `institution of the suit;`
  line
  line `(2) that the parties are within the prohibited degree of consanguinity (whether natural or legal)`
  line `or affinity;`
  line
  line `(3) that either party was a lunatic or idiot at the time of the marriage;`
  line
  line `(4) that the former husband or wife of either party was living at the time of the marriage, and`
  line `the marriage with such former husband or wife was then in force.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall affect the ^1[jurisdiction of the District Court] to make decrees of`
  line `nullity of marriage on the ground that the consent of either party was obtained by force or fraud.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (46396)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46396&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `[Confirmation of District Judge's decree.]—Omitted by the Indian Divorce (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2001 (51 of 2001), s. 16 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (46397)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Children of annulled marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46397&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where a marriage is annulled on the ground that a former`
  line `husband or wife was living, and it is adjudged that the subsequent marriage was contracted in good`
  line `faith and with the full belief of the parties that the former husband or wife was dead, or when a`
  line `marriage is annulled on the ground of insanity, children begotten before the decree is made shall be`
  line `specified in the decree, and shall be entitled to succeed, in the same manner as legitimate children, to`
  line `the estate of the parent who at the time of the marriage was competent to contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (46463)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Bar to decree for divorce a mensa et toro; but judicial separation obtainable by husband or wife`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. The words "without reasonable excuse" omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46463&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No decree shall hereafter be made for a divorce a mensa et toro, but the husband or wife`
  line `may obtain a decree of judicial separation, on the ground of adultery, or cruelty, or desertion ^1`
  line `*** for`
  line `two years or upwards, and such decree shall have the effect of a divorce a mensa et toro under the`
  line `existing law, and such other legal effect as here in after mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (46399)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Application for separation made by petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or to the High Court" omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 18 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46399&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Application for judicial separation on any`
  line `one of the grounds aforesaid, may be made by either husband or wife by petition to the District Court`
  line ^1
  line `***, and the Court, on being satisfied of the truth of the statements made in such petition, and that`
  line `there is no legal ground why the application should not be granted, may decree judicial separation`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (46400)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Separated wife deemed spinster with respect to after-acquired property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46400&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `In every case`
  line `of a judicial separation under this Act, the wife shall from the date of the sentence, and whilst the`
  line `separation continues, be considered as unmarried with respect to property of every description which`
  line `she may acquire, or which may come to or devolve upon her.`
  line
  line `Such property may be disposed of by her in all respects as an unmarried woman, and on her`
  line `decease the same shall, in case she dies intestate, go as the same would have gone if her husband had`
  line `been then dead:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if any such wife again cohabits with her husband, all such property as she may be`
  line `entitled to when such cohabitation takes place shall be held to her separate use, subject, however, to`
  line `any agreement in writing made between herself and her husband whilst separate.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (46401)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Separated wife deemed spinster for purposes of contract and suing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46401&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `In every case of a`
  line `judicial separation under this Act, the wife shall, whilst so separated, be considered as an unmarried`
  line `woman for the purposes of contract, and wrongs and injuries, and suing and being sued in any civil`
  line `proceedings; and her husband shall not be liable in respect of any contact, act or costs entered into,`
  line `done, omitted or incurred by her during the separation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, upon any such judicial separation, alimony has been decreed or ordered to be`
  line `paid to the wife, and the same is not duly paid by the husband, he shall be liable for necessaries`
  line `supplied for her use:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing shall prevent the wife from joining, at any time during such separation,`
  line `in the exercise of any joint power given to herself and her husband.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (46402)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Decree of separation obtained during absence of husband or wife may be reversed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46402&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Any husband or wife, upon the application of whose wife or husband, as the case may`
  line `be, a decree of judicial separation has been pronounced, may, at any time thereafter, present a petition`
  line `to the Court by which the decree was pronounced, praying for a reversal of such decree, on the ground`
  line `that it was obtained in his or her absence, and that there was reasonable excuse for the alleged`
  line `desertion, where desertion was the ground of such decree.`
  line
  line `The Court may, on being satisfied of the truth of the allegations of such petition reverse the decree`
  line `accordingly; but such reversal shall not prejudice or affect the rights or remedies which any other`
  line `person would have had, in case it had not been decreed, in respect of any debts, contracts, or acts of`
  line `the wife incurred, entered into, or done between the times of the sentence of separation and of the`
  line `reversal thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (46454)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Deserted wife may apply to court for protection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46454&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any wife to whom section 4 of the`
  line `Indian Succession Act, 1865 (10 of 1865) ^1`
  line `does not apply, may, when deserted by her husband,`
  line `present a petition to the District Court ^2`
  line `***, at any time after such desertion, for an order to protect`
  line `any property which she may have acquired or may acquire, and any property of which she may have`
  line `become possessed or may become possessed after such desertion, against her husband or his creditors,`
  line `or any person claiming under him.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925).`
  line `2. The words or the High Court omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 18 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (46404)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Court may grant protection-order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46404&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Court, if satisfied of the fact of such desertion, and`
  line `that the same was without reasonable excuse, and that the wife is maintaining herself by her own`
  line `industry or property, may make and give to the wife an order protecting her earnings and other`
  line `property from her husband and all creditors and persons claiming under him. Every such order shall`
  line `state the time at which the desertion commenced, and shall, as regards all persons dealing with the`
  line `wife in reliance thereon, be conclusive as to such time.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (46405)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Discharge or variation of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46405&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The husband or any creditor of, or person claiming under`
  line `him, may apply to the Court by which such order was made for the discharge or variation thereof, and`
  line `the Court, if the desertion has ceased, or if for any other reason it thinks fit so to do, may discharge or`
  line `vary the order accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (46406)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Liability of husband seizing wife’s property after notice of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46406&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If the husband, or any`
  line `creditor of, or person claiming under, the husband, seizes or continues to hold any property of the`
  line `wife after notice of any such order, he shall be liable, at the suit of the wife (which she is hereby`
  line `empowered to bring), to return or deliver to her the specific property, and also to pay her a sum equal`
  line `to double its value.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (46407)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Wife’s legal position during continuance of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46407&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `So long as any such order of protection`
  line `remains in force the wife shall be and be deemed to have been, during such desertion of her, in the like position in all respects, with regard to property and contracts and suing and being sued, as she`
  line `would be under this Act if she obtained a decree of judicial separation.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (46464)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Petition for restitution of conjugal rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. The words “or the High Court” omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 18 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46464&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `When either the husband or the wife has,`
  line `without reasonable excuse, withdrawn from the society of the other, either wife, or husband may`
  line `apply, by petition to the District Court ^1`
  line `*** for restitution of conjugal rights, and the Court, on being`
  line `satisfied of the truth of the statements made in such petition, and that there is no legal ground why the`
  line `application should not be granted, may decree restitution of conjugal rights accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (46409)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Answer to petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46409&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Nothing shall be pleaded in answer to a petition for restitution of`
  line `conjugal rights, which would not be ground for a suit for judicial separation or for a decree of nullity`
  line `of marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (46462)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46462&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `[Husband may claim damages from adulterer.]--Omitted by the Indian Divorce`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2001 (51 of 2001), s. 19 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (46411)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Power to order adulterer to pay costs.]--Omitted by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46411&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (46459)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Alimony pendente lite.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46459&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `In any suit under this Act, whether it be instituted by a husband or a`
  line `wife, and whether or not she has obtained an order of protection ^1[the wife may present a petition for`
  line `expenses of the proceedings and alimony pending the suit.]`
  line
  line `Such petition shall be served on the husband; and the Court, on being satisfied of the truth of the`
  line `statements therein contained, may make such order on the husband ^2[for payment to the wife of the`
  line `expenses of the proceedings and alimony pending the suit] alimony pending the suit as it may deem`
  line `just:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[Provided further that the petition for the expenses of the proceedings and alimony pending the`
  line `suit, shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within sixty days of service of such petition on the`
  line husband.]
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 2, for "the wife may present a petition for alimony pending the suit" (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "for payment to the wife of alimony pending the suit" (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  line `3. The proviso omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 21 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (46413)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to order permanent alimony.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 22, for certain words (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46413&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where a decree of dissolution of the marriage or a`
  line `decree of judicial separation is obtained by the wife, the District Court may order that the husband`
  line `shall] to the satisfaction of the court, secure to the wife such gross sum of money, or such annual sum`
  line `of money for any term not exceeding her own life, as, having regard to her fortune (if any), to the`
  line `ability of the husband, and to the conduct of the parties, it thinks reasonable; and for that purpose may`
  line `cause a proper instrument to be executed by all necessary parties.`
  line
  line `Power to order monthly or weekly payments.-- In every such case the Court may make an`
  line `order on the husband for payment to the wife of such monthly or weekly sums for her maintenance`
  line `and support as the Court may think reasonable:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the husband afterwards from any cause becomes unable to make such payments, it`
  line `shall be lawful for the Court to discharge or modify the order, or temporarily to suspend the same as`
  line `to the whole or any part of the money so ordered to be paid, and again to revive the same order wholly`
  line `or in part as to the court seems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (46414)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Court may direct payment of alimony to wife or to her trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46414&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `In all cases in which the`
  line `Court makes any decree or order for alimony, it may direct the same to be paid either to the wife`
  line `herself, or to any trustee on her behalf to be approved by the court, and may impose any terms or`
  line `restrictions which to the Court seem expedient, and may from time to time appoint a new trustee, if it`
  line `appears to the Court expedient so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (46461)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46461&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `[ Power to order settlement of wife's property for benefit of husband and children.]--Omitted`
  line `by the Indian Divorce (Amendment) Act, 2001 (51 of 2001), s. 23 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (46416)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Inquiry into existence of ante-nuptial or post-nuptial settlements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 24, for certain words (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46416&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^1[The District Court`
  line `may, before passing a decree for dissolution of the marriage or a decree of nullity of marriage, inquire`
  line `into] the existence of ante-nuptial or post-nuptial settlements made on the parties whose marriage is`
  line `the subject of the decree, and may make such orders, with reference to the application of the whole or`
  line `a portion of the property settled, whether for the benefit of the husband or the wife, or of the children`
  line `(if any) of the marriage, or of both children and parents, as to the Court seems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court shall not make any order for the benefit of the parents or either of them at`
  line `the expense of the children.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (46456)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to make orders as to custody of children in suit for separation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46456&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `In any suit for`
  line `obtaining a judicial separation the Court may from time to time, before making its decree, make such`
  line `interim orders, and may make such provision in the decree, as it deems proper with respect to the`
  line `custody, maintenance and education of the minor children, the marriage of whose parents is the`
  line `subject of such suit, and may, if it thinks fit, direct proceedings to be taken for placing such children`
  line `under the protection of the said Court:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the application with respect to the maintenance and education of the minor children`
  line `pending the suit, shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within sixty days from the date of service of`
  line `notice on the respondent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (46418)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to make such orders after decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46418&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The court, after a decree of judicial separation,`
  line `may upon application (by petition) for this purpose make, from time to time, all such orders and`
  line `provisions, with respect to the custody, maintenance and education of the minor children, the marriage`
  line `of whose parents is the subject of the decree, or for placing such children under the protection of the`
  line `said court, as might have been made by such decree or by interim orders in case the proceedings for`
  line `obtaining such decree were still pending.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (46419)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to make orders as to custody of children in suits for dissolution or nullity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 25, for certain words (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46419&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line ^1[In
  line `any suit for obtaining a dissolution of marriage or a decree of nullity of marriage instituted in a`
  line `District Court, the Court may from time to time before making its decree, make such interim orders as`
  line `it may deem proper] with respect to the custody, maintenance and education of the minor children, the`
  line `marriage of whose parents is the subject of the suit,`
  line
  line `and may, if it thinks fit, direct proceedings to be taken for placing such children under the`
  line `protection of the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (46420)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to make such orders after decree or confirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by, s. 26, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46420&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where a decree of`
  line `dissolution or nullity of marriage has been passed, the District Court may, upon application] by`
  line `petition for the purpose, make from time to time all such orders and provisions, with respect to the`
  line `custody, maintenance and education of the minor children, the marriage of whose parents was the`
  line `subject of the decree, or for placing such children under the protection of the said court, as might have been made by such decree absolute or decree (as the case may be), or by such interim orders as`
  line aforesaid.
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (46455)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `Code of Civil Procedure to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 27, for "Code of Civil Procedure" (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46455&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions herein contained, all`
  line `proceedings under this Act between party and party shall be regulated by the ^1[Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).]`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (46422)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Forms of petitions and statements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46422&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The forms set forth in the Schedule to this Act, with`
  line `such variation as the circumstances of each case require, may be used for the respective purposes`
  line `mentioned in such Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (46423)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 49
  title `Petition to state absence of collusion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46423&sectionno=47&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Every petition under this Act for a decree of`
  line `dissolution of marriage, or of nullity of marriage, or of judicial separation ^1`
  line `*** shall ^2`
  line `*** state that`
  line `there is not any collusion or connivance between the petitioner and the other party to the marriage.`
  line
  line `Statements to be verified.--The statements contained in every petition under this Act shall be`
  line `verified by the petitioner or some other competent person in manner required by law for the`
  line `verification of plaints, and may at the hearing be referred to as evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The Words "or of reversal of judicial separation, or for restitution of conjugal rights, or for damages, shall bear a stamp of`
  line `five rupees, and" rep. by Act 7 of 1870, s. 2 and the Schedule III.`
  line `2. The words "in the first, second and third cases mentioned in this section," rep. by Act 7 of 1870, s. 2 and the Schedule III.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (46424)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 50
  title `Suits on behalf of lunatics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46424&sectionno=48&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `When the husband or wife is a lunatic or idiot, any suit under`
  line `this Act (other than a suit for restitution of conjugal rights) may be brought on his or her behalf by the`
  line `committee or other person entitled to his or her custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (46425)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 51
  title `Suits by minors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. The words “shall bear a stamp of eight annas and” rep. by Act 7 of 1870, s. 2 and the Schedule III.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46425&sectionno=49&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where the petitioner is a minor, he or she shall sue by his or her next friend`
  line `to be approved by the Court; and no petition presented by a minor under this Act shall be filed until`
  line `the next friend has undertaken in writing to be answerable for costs.`
  line `Such undertaking ^1`
  line `*** shall be filed in Court, and the next friend shall thereupon be liable in the same`
  line `manner and to the same extent as if he were a plaintiff in an ordinary suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (46426)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 52
  title `Service of petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for the Provinces, which had been substituted by the A.O. 1948, for "British India".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46426&sectionno=50&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Every petition under this Act shall be served on the party to be affected`
  line `thereby, either within or without ^1[India], in such manner as the High Court by general or special`
  line `order from time to time directs.`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may dispense with such service altogether in case it seems necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (46427)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 53
  title `Mode of taking evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46427&sectionno=51&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The witnesses in all proceedings before the court, where their`
  line `attendance can be had, shall be examined orally, and any party may offer himself or herself as a`
  line `witness, and shall be examined, and may be cross-examined and re-examined, like any other witness:`
  line
  line `Provided that the parties shall be at liberty to verify their respective cases in whole or in part by`
  line `affidavit, but so that the deponent in every such affidavit shall, on the application of the opposite`
  line `party, or by direction of the Court, be subject to be cross-examined by or on behalf of the opposite`
  line `party orally, and after such cross-examination may be re-examined orally as aforesaid by or on behalf`
  line `of the party by whom such affidavit was filed.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (46428)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 54
  title `Competence of husband and wife to give evidence as to cruelty or desertion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 28, for certain words (w.e.f 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46428&sectionno=52&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `On any`
  line `petition presented, ^1[by a husband or a wife, praying that his or her marriage may be dissolved by`
  line `reason of his wife or her husband, as the case may be, having been guilty of adultery, cruelty or`
  line `desertion], the husband and wife respectively shall be competent and compellable to give evidence of`
  line `or relating to such cruelty or desertion.`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (46429)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to close doors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46429&sectionno=53&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The whole or any part of any proceeding under this Act may be heard,`
  line `if the Court thinks fit, with closed doors.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (46430)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to adjourn.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46430&sectionno=54&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The Court may, from time to time, adjourn the hearing of any petition`
  line `under this Act, and may require further evidence thereon if it sees fit so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (46431)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 57
  title `Enforcement of, and appeals from, orders and decrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46431&sectionno=55&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `All decrees and orders made by the`
  line `Court in any suit or proceedings under this Act shall be enforced and may be appealed from, in the`
  line `like manner as the decrees and orders of the Court made in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction`
  line `are enforced and may be appealed from, under the laws, rules and orders for the time being in`
  line `force:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `No appeal as to costs.--^2[Provided] that there shall be no appeal on the subject of costs only.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The first proviso omitted by Act 51 of 2001, s. 29 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for "Provided also" (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (46432)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 58
  title `Appeal to the Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Her Majesty in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46432&sectionno=56&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Any person may appeal to ^1[the Supreme Court] from any`
  line `decree (other than a decree nisi) or order under this Act of a High Court made on appeal or otherwise,`
  line `and from any decree (other than a decree nisi) or order made in the exercise of original jurisdiction`
  line `by Judges of a High Court or of any Division Court from which an appeal shall not lie to the High`
  line Court,
  line `when the High Court declares that the case is a fit one for appeal to ^1[the Supreme Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (46457)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 59
  title `Liberty to parties to marry again.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 30, for section 57 (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46457&sectionno=57&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `^1[57. Liberty to parties to marry again.— Where a decree for dissolution or nullity of marriage`
  line `has been passed and either the time for appeal has expired without an appeal having been presented to`
  line `any court including the Supreme Court or an appeal has been presented but has been dismissed and`
  line `the decree or dismissal has become final, it shall be lawful for either party to the marriage to marry`
  line again.]
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (46434)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 60
  title `English clergyman not compelled to solemnize marriages of persons divorced for adultery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46434&sectionno=58&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `No clergyman in Holy Orders of the ^1`
  line `*** Church of England ^2`
  line `*** shall be compelled to`
  line `solemnize the marriage of any-person whose former marriage has been dissolved on the ground of his`
  line `or her adultery, or shall be liable to any suit, penalty or censure for solemnizing or refusing to`
  line `solemnize the marriage of any such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "United" rep. by Act 12 of 1873, s. 1 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. The words "and Ireland" rep. by s. 1, ibid. and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (46435)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 61
  title `English Minister refusing to perform ceremony to permit use of his Church.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. The word "United" rep. by Act 12 of 1873, s. 1 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46435&sectionno=59&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `When any`
  line `Minister of any Church or Chapel of the said ^1`
  line `*** Church refuses to perform such marriage-service`
  line `between any persons who but for such refusal would be entitled to have the same service performed in`
  line `such Church or Chapel, such Minister shall permit any other Minister in Holy Orders of the said`
  line `Church, entitled to officiate within the diocese in which such Church or Chapel is situate, to perform`
  line `such marriage-service in such Church or Chapel.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (46460)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 62
  title `Decree for separation or protection-order valid as to persons dealing with wife before reversal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46460&sectionno=60&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Every decree for judicial separation or order to protect property, obtained by a wife`
  line `under this Act shall, until reversed or discharged, be deemed valid, so far as necessary, for the`
  line `protection of any person dealing with the wife.`
  line
  line `No reversal, discharge or variation of such decree or order shall affect any rights or remedies`
  line `which any person would otherwise have had in respect of any contracts or acts of the wife entered into`
  line `or done between the dates of such decree or order, and of the reversal, discharge or variation thereof.`
  line
  line `Indemnity of persons making payment to wife without notice of reversal of decree or`
  line `protection order.-- All persons who in reliance on any such decree or order make any payment to,`
  line `or permit any transfer or act to be made or done by, the wife who has obtained the same shall,`
  line `notwithstanding such decree or order may then have been reversed, discharged or varied, or the`
  line `separation of the wife from her husband may have ceased, or at some time since the making of the decree or order been discontinued, be protected and indemnified as if, at the time of such payment,`
  line `transfer or other act, such decree or order were valid and still subsisting without variation, and the`
  line `separation had not ceased or been discontinued,`
  line
  line `unless, at the time of the payment, transfer or other act, such persons had notice of the reversal,`
  line `discharge or variation of the decree or order or of the cessation or discontinuance of the separation.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (46437)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 63
  title `Bar of suit for criminal conversation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46437&sectionno=61&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `After this Act comes into operation, no person`
  line `competent to present a petition under sections 2 and 10 shall maintain a suit for criminal conversation`
  line `with his wife.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (46438)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 64
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 2001, s. 31, for Code of Civil Procedure (w.e.f. 3-10-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865&sectionId=46438&sectionno=62&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00033_186904_1523268113865
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `The High Court shall make such rules under this Act as it may from`
  line `time to time consider expedient, and may from time to time alter and add to the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that such rules, alterations and additions are consistent with the provisions of this Act and`
  line `the ^1[Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908)].`
  line
  line `All such rules, alteration and additions shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
